  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#W020">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#PatientCondition"/>
    <rdfs:label>W020</rdfs:label>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R026"/>
    <hasWarningHeadline>Sodium Content</hasWarningHeadline>
    <hasWarningText>Before receiving IVOZFO, notify the doctor if the patient have any of the following health conditions: heart problems, high blood pressure, hyperaldosteronism which is a condition where you have too much of a hormone called aldosterone, cirrhosis (scar tissue) of the liver, kidney problems, high levels of sodium in the blood, or fluid in your lungs. IVOZFO contains sodium that could make these conditions worse.</hasWarningText>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#HepatobiliaryDisorder">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#SideEffect"/>
    <rdfs:label>Hepatobiliary Disorder</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#R042">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Reference"/>
    <rdfs:label>R042</rdfs:label>
    <hasAuthor>National Library of Medicine</hasAuthor>
    <retrievedFrom>https://medlineplus.gov/ency/article/000145.htm</retrievedFrom>
    <publishedIn rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">2024</publishedIn>
    <hasReferenceTitle>Community-acquired pneumonia in adults</hasReferenceTitle>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#SE227">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Rash"/>
    <rdfs:label>Rash</rdfs:label>
    <hasDuration>Not specified</hasDuration>
    <whichIs rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Common"/>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R116"/>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R035"/>
    <hasSideEffectDescription>Skin rashes can be red, inflamed, bumpy as well as dry, itchy or painful. The main cause is dermatitis, which is when your skin reacts to allergens or irritants. Bacteria, viruses, allergens and conditions including eczema, hives, and psoriasis can be the source of skin rashes.</hasSideEffectDescription>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#ITN249">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Interaction"/>
    <rdfs:label>ITN249</rdfs:label>
    <hasClinicalEffects>Because less Macrobid reaches your bloodstream and urine, the infection may not get treated properly. You may have ongoing symptoms of urinary tract infection like pain, burning, or frequent urination.</hasClinicalEffects>
    <hasInteractionDescription>Antacids that contain magnesium trisilicate can stick to Macrobid in your stomach and gut, which lowers the amount of the antibiotic that your body can absorb. This makes Macrobid less able to fight the bacteria causing your infection.</hasInteractionDescription>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R161"/>
    <interactsWith rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#S168"/>
    <hasManagementAdvice>Avoid taking these antacids while on Macrobid. If you must take an antacid, separate the doses by at least 2-3 hours. Always tell your doctor or pharmacist about any antacids you are using.</hasManagementAdvice>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#SE335">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Eosinophilia"/>
    <rdfs:label>eosinophilia</rdfs:label>
    <hasDuration>Not Specified</hasDuration>
    <hasSideEffectDescription>increase of circulating eosinophils &gt;500 /mm^3</hasSideEffectDescription>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R191"/>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R011"/>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R077"/>
    <whichIs rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#not_Specified"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#SE290">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#TorsadeDePointes"/>
    <rdfs:label>Torsade de pointes</rdfs:label>
    <hasDuration>During treatment</hasDuration>
    <hasSideEffectDescription>A life-threatening, polymorphic ventricular tachycardia that must be monitored in high-risk patients.</hasSideEffectDescription>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R054"/>
    <whichIs rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Very_rare"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#SP163">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Storage"/>
    <rdfs:label>SP163</rdfs:label>
    <hasStewardshipDescription>Store nitrofurantoin in a cool, dry place at room temperature, away from direct sunlight, moisture, or heat. Proper storage helps maintain the effectiveness and safety of the medication throughout its shelf life.</hasStewardshipDescription>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R157"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#SE490">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#RenalImpairment"/>
    <rdfs:label>Renal Impairment</rdfs:label>
    <whichIs rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Not_Specified"/>
    <hasDuration>Not Specified</hasDuration>
    <hasSideEffectDescription>a condition in which one or both of your kidneys no longer work on their own.</hasSideEffectDescription>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R141"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#SE040">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#AbdominalPain"/>
    <rdfs:label>Abdominal Pain</rdfs:label>
    <hasDuration>Not Specified</hasDuration>
    <hasSideEffectDescription>Effects are usually mild; pain felt anywhere between the chest and groin.</hasSideEffectDescription>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R037"/>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R058"/>
    <whichIs rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Common"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#W042">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#AgeRestriction"/>
    <rdfs:label>W042</rdfs:label>
    <hasWarningText>Safety and effectiveness of CONTEPO in patients less than 18 years of age has not been established.</hasWarningText>
    <hasWarningHeadline>Pediatric Use</hasWarningHeadline>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R028"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#SE569">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Diarrhea"/>
    <rdfs:label>diarrhea</rdfs:label>
    <hasDuration>Not Specified</hasDuration>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R008"/>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R207"/>
    <hasSideEffectDescription>having a loose, watery stool during a bowel movement</hasSideEffectDescription>
    <whichIs rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Common"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#ITN088">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Interaction"/>
    <rdfs:label>ITN088</rdfs:label>
    <hasInteractionDescription>Concomitant use of trimethoprim with digoxin has been shown to increase plasma digoxin levels in a proportion of elderly patients. Serum digoxin levels should be monitored.</hasInteractionDescription>
    <interactsWith rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#S062"/>
    <hasClinicalEffects>Digoxin toxicity which includes nausea, arrhythmias</hasClinicalEffects>
    <hasManagementAdvice>Monitor serum digoxin. Adjust dose to avoid toxicity.</hasManagementAdvice>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R035"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#ITN024">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Interaction"/>
    <rdfs:label>ITN024</rdfs:label>
    <hasManagementAdvice>Monitor INR/blood clotting; adjust warfarin dose if necessary.</hasManagementAdvice>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R028"/>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R027"/>
    <interactsWith rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#S018"/>
    <hasClinicalEffects>Prolonged bleeding or easy bruising.</hasClinicalEffects>
    <hasInteractionDescription>May increase risk of bleeding when used together.</hasInteractionDescription>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#SE604">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#VentricularArrhythmia"/>
    <rdfs:label>ventricular arrhythmia</rdfs:label>
    <hasSideEffectDescription>abnormal heart rhythms that make the lower chambers of your heart twitch instead of pump</hasSideEffectDescription>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R008"/>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R239"/>
    <hasDuration>Not Specified</hasDuration>
    <whichIs rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Uncommon"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#R274">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Reference"/>
    <rdfs:label>R274</rdfs:label>
    <retrievedFrom>https://emedicine.medscape.com/article/2040035-overview</retrievedFrom>
    <hasAuthor>Medscape</hasAuthor>
    <hasReferenceTitle>Catheter-Related Urinary Tract Infection (UTI)</hasReferenceTitle>
    <publishedIn rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">2025</publishedIn>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#ITN073">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Interaction"/>
    <rdfs:label>ITN073</rdfs:label>
    <hasManagementAdvice>Consider additional contraceptive measures</hasManagementAdvice>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R017"/>
    <hasClinicalEffects>May cause breakthrough bleeding and reduce birth control effectiveness</hasClinicalEffects>
    <interactsWith rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#S047"/>
    <hasInteractionDescription>Concomitant use with penicillins</hasInteractionDescription>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#SE672">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Tendonitis"/>
    <rdfs:label>tendonitis</rdfs:label>
    <hasDuration>Not Specified</hasDuration>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R251"/>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R008"/>
    <whichIs rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Uncommon"/>
    <hasSideEffectDescription>the connective tissues between your muscles and bones (tendons) inflame</hasSideEffectDescription>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#W178">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#PatientCondition"/>
    <rdfs:label>W178</rdfs:label>
    <hasWarningText>Although levofloxacin is more soluble than other quinolones, adequate hydration of patients receiving levofloxacin should be maintained to prevent the formation of highly concentrated urine.</hasWarningText>
    <hasWarningHeadline>Maintained Hydration</hasWarningHeadline>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R008"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#I013">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#NonGonococcalUrethritis"/>
    <rdfs:label>Non-gonococcal urethritis</rdfs:label>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R038"/>
    <hasReference rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#R045"/>
    <hasSeverityType rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#NotSpecified"/>
    <hasSymptoms>Men: Discharge from penis, pain while peeing (dysuria), pain while ejaculating (dysorgasmia or orgasmalgia), itching, irritation and/or tenderness, abdominal pain. Women: Vaginal discharge, pain while peeing, pain during sexual intercourse (dyspareunia), spotting or cramping throughout the month (irregular periods).</hasSymptoms>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/ontology#ITN012">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/ontology#Interaction"/>
    <rdfs:label>ITN012</rdfs:label>
    <hasClinicalEffects>Higher risk of kidney damage.</hasClinicalEffects>
